DataElementConcept.preferredName: Glucose Measurement Greater Than or Equal To One Hundred Fifty Milligram per Deciliter Level
DataElementConcept.preferredDefinition: The determination of the amount of glucose present in a sample._A statement about the relative size or order of two objects specifying that either both objects are the same in quantity or measure or value or status or that the object of interest exceeds the other object in one of these ways._A natural number greater than 149 and less than 151 and the quantity that it denotes._A unit of mass concentration defined as the concentration of one milligram of a substance in unit volume of the mixture equal to one cubic deciliter or 100 cubic centimeters. It is also a unit of mass density (volumic mass) defined as the density of substance which mass equal to one milligram occupies the volume one cubic deciliter or 100 cubic centimeters._A position on a scale measuring intensity, quality, or amount.
